parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size. Defaults to 200 if not provided. Maximum of 5000

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page number. Defaults to 1 if not provided

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: “The CEQL search expression. Only the '=' operator is supported, with the following queryable fields (ranges). An example may be, ranges = 'sheet3' wherein only sheet3 properties are retrieved, (here, ranges refers to a worksheet name). If not specified, it retrieves all the sheets with properties”

parameters.name: range
parameters.description: The worksheet data range. For example, if the worksheet data is: A1=1,B1=2,A2=3,B2=4, then requesting range=A1:B1, It clears [[1,2]]

resources.description: Retrieve the content of a worksheet

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression. Only the '=' operator is supported, with the following queryable fields (majorDimension). An example may be majorDimension = 'ROWS' it retrieves data based on ROWS

parameters.name: range
parameters.description: The worksheet data range. For example, if the worksheet data is: A1=1,B1=2,A2=3,B2=4, then requesting range=A1:B2,majorDimension=ROWS will return [[1,2],[3,4]], whereas requesting range=A1:B2,majorDimension=COLUMNS will return [[1,3],[2,4]]

resources.description: Update the content of a worksheet

parameters.name: range
parameters.description: The worksheet data range. For example, if the worksheet data is: A1=1,B1=2,A2=3,B2=4, then requesting range=A1:B2,majorDimension=ROWS will updates [[1,2],[3,4]], whereas requesting range=A1:B2,majorDimension=COLUMNS will updates [[1,3],[2,4]]

resources.description: Create the row for a worksheet.
Delete the row for a worksheet.

parameters.name: cellId
parameters.description: The worksheet data cellId. For example, if the worksheet data is: A1=1,B1=2,C1=3,A2=4,B2=5,C3=6 [A,B,C represents Columns ... 1,2,3 represents Rows] If cellId=A1, it clears the complete 1st row from column A, If cellId=C3,  it clears the complete 3rd row from column C

resources.description: Retrieve the row for a worksheet
